Trainer
Confidential Company - ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/29 10:00:33
Ref. JB3045389
Job Description
Our client, a diversified holding company with operations in the Middle East in the automobile sales and service, luxury and lifestyle retail, engineering and interiors contracting, is looking for a TRAINER to be based in its headquarters in Dubai, UAE.
Job purpose:
•	To design and deliver suitable training programs to support the organization’s development objectives and to enable establishment of a learning culture.
Job description:
•	Support the Line Managers in identifying training needs, deciding on the type and number of training courses required.
•	Identify and develop training programs and material in line with business needs and corporate training and development policies.
•	Conduct the induction program, as required, for new joiners by providing them in-depth information on the products, job responsibilities, customer service standards and policies and procedures.
•	Facilitate the training program and deliver training courses to meet its stated objectives and motivate the attendees to imbibe the learning and apply it in the workplace.
Skills
The successful candidate will have 5-10 years of experience in various aspects of training – planning, designing, delivery and administration, keeps abreast of development in training tools and learning aids, and has a strong understanding of learning management systems. You should have Excellent Presentation, Communication and Interpersonal skills and proficient in English language. You would have qualification in Training/Human Resources. Preferably Westerner.
Salary range: AED 16,000 – 20,000 per month plus other benefits
Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.
